\begin_layout Section
Abstract
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Dense genes in bacterial genomes feature bacterial transcriptome maps.
 High-throughput sequencing of messenger RNAs allows us to map bacterial
 transcriptomes.
 Modified RNAs preparation with high-throughput sequencing allow us to different
 perspective RNA transcriptome.
 RNAs preparation can enrich small RNAs, or transcript starting regions.
 Enrichment of whole messenger RNAs are necessary to quantify expression
 levels of genes.
 This enrichment technique makes it difficult to predict transcript boundaries
 that can include multiple genes.
 Although a method based on hidden Markov model was developed to infer transcrip
t boundaries, variation of boundaries estimates has been remained to quantify.
 We develop a Bayesian approach to quantifying uncertainty of inferred trasncrip
t boundaries using RNA-seq.
 The approach would facilitate more informed decision of predicted transcript
 boundaries.
\end_layout

