\begin_layout Standard
The Dirichlet distribution of order K ≥ 2 with parameters α1, ..., αK > 0 has
 a probability density function with respect to Lebesgue measure on the
 Euclidean space RK-1 given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\left(x_{1},\ldots,x_{K-1};\alpha_{1},\ldots,\alpha_{K}\right)=\frac{\Gamma\left(\sum_{k}\alpha_{k}\right)}{\prod_{k}\Gamma\left(\alpha_{k}\right)}\prod_{k=1}^{K}x_{k}^{\alpha_{k}-1}
\]

\end_inset

for all positive 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1},\ldots,x_{K-1}$
\end_inset

 satisfying 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{k=1}^{K-1}x_{k}=x_{K}<1.$
\end_inset

